    <p>New Week­end Brunch At Raf­fles Court­yard</p>
    <p>You can en­joy fresh patis­series straight from the bak­ery, lo­cal de­lights and con­tem­po­rary dishes, as well as bev­er­ages such as smooth­ies and a se­lec­tion of the Raf­fles blend of tea and cof­fee. You can also cre­ate your own Court­yard brunch by se­lect­ing one main course and one cold and one hot bev­er­age for $28++.</p>
    <p>Raf­fles Ar­cade, 328 North Bridge Road City Hall</p>
    <p>Sat & Sun, 9.30am - 3pm 6412-1816 E-mail sin­ga­pore@raf­fles.com</p>
    <p>Hai Tien Lo Re­opens With New Dine-in Ex­pe­ri­ence</p>
    <p>At award-win­ning Can­tonese restau­rant Hai Tien Lo, a la carte and set menus will be avail­able for lunch and din­ner through­out the week. Dim sum lovers can in­dulge in a cu­rated a la carte dim sum menu on week­days and a dim sum brunch buf­fet on week­ends.</p>
    <p>Hai Tien Lo, Pan Pa­cific Sin­ga­pore, Ma­rina Square, 7 Raf­fles Boule­vard Es­planade</p>
    <p>From to­day, lunch: 11.30am - 2.30pm, din­ner: 6 - 10pm; closed on Wed From $58 a diner (min­i­mum of two din­ers) for lunch set</p>


